                <h2 class="writing-title">On Simplicity</h2>
                <div class="writing-content">
                    <p>
                        The best interfaces disappear. Not literally—though sometimes that helps—but cognitively. 
                        They become invisible extensions of intent. When someone uses your product and says 
                        "it just works," that's the highest compliment.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Simplicity isn't minimalism.</strong> It's clarity of purpose. A dense dashboard 
                        can be simple if every element serves the user's goal. An empty screen can be complex 
                        if it leaves users guessing.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

