                <div class="writing-content">
                    <p>
                        Every semester at Northwestern, I'm reminded that teaching is the best way to stay sharp. 
                        Students ask questions you stopped asking. They see problems you've learned to ignore.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Fresh eyes are a superpower.</strong> When a student asks "why does it work this way?" 
                        and you realize you don't have a good answer, that's where innovation lives.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

