                <h2 class="writing-title">Side Projects as R&D</h2>
                <div class="writing-content">
                    <p>
                        Mantras.guru taught me about internationalization. Cadence.cards about spaced repetition algorithms. 
                        Cerca.me about location-based services. None of these were the goal—they were discoveries along the way.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Build to learn, not to launch.</strong> The pressure to ship kills experimentation. 
                        Some of my best professional work came from techniques discovered in "failed" side projects.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

